rows.title: IT Database Administrator
rows.description:
Job Responsibilities

1. Responsible for the maintenance of cloud-based databases such as MySQL, SQL Server, Redis, etc.

2. Design appropriate database structures and table relationships to meet business requirements while ensuring data consistency.

3. Develop and execute database backup and recovery strategies as per requirements, ensuring data safety and availability.

4. Analyze and optimize complex queries, design and maintain indexes to enhance query performance.

5. Manage database monitoring, diagnose and resolve failures, ensuring high system availability and stability.

6. Configure and manage database permissions and access control to ensure data security.

7. Assist the development team with database-related design and development tasks, providing technical support and guidance.

8. Participate in formulating database architecture and disaster recovery plans to ensure system resilience and scalability.

9. Collaborate with the team to resolve database-related issues, continuously optimizing database performance and operational processes.

10. Keep track of new technologies and trends in the database field, continuously updating and enhancing technical knowledge.



Skill Requirements

1. Database Management Systems: Familiarity with MySQL, SQL Server, Redis, etc. Understanding their features, pros and cons, and suitable use cases.

2. SQL Writing and Optimization: Proficiency in efficiently writing and optimizing complex SQL queries. Capable of query performance optimization, including table structure design, index design, query plan analysis, etc.

3. Backup and Recovery: Ability to formulate and execute database backup and recovery strategies to ensure data integrity and availability.

4. Performance Optimization: Monitoring and analyzing database performance, identifying bottlenecks, and providing optimization recommendations for ensuring stable and high-performance system operation.
